6:
You totally should've been there. He
was all, don't go there, don't do that,
blah-blah-blah.
10:
I wanted to be like, GRANDPA! How
old do you think I am?! I am the
definition of a strong independent
wo—
20:
What the hell?! Watch where you're
swimming!
25:
Right back at you! Do you have, like,
two left... fins?
32: O. EM. GEE. What are you?!
38:
Okay, what's with the attitude?! If
you think you can scare me, mister,
you have another thing—AH!
43: Must've inhaled the stuff I dropped.
53:
Goodbye, cruel world... The waves
are so cold...
55:
I only wish... I could've died in
Czarina's warm embrace...
65:
Cut the drama and follow me. We've
got time to save her.
74:
No crap. What kind of idiot develops
poison without an antidote?
78:
Uh, what I want to know is why
you're making poison in the first
place.
81:
It's a by-product, okay? I'm doing
research on myself.
84:
As you can see, I'm not a human or
a fish or even a flippin' dolphin. I'm
not mer- or beastfolk either. I'm a
damn enigma I've been trying to
solve for years.
88:
*sniff* I could've, like, never
imagined you'd have such a tragic
backstory.
91:
Al? Lighteous? We HAVE to help him
out.
96: Yeah, sure. I'll do what I can.
100:
So, my name's Amelia... And that's Al
and Lighteous.
103: She means we're Alk and Light.
108:
I don't get it. What's got you
interested in my plight?
111:
Well, Al here has amnesia, so both of
you don't know who you are! And
you and I are aquatic critter
buddies! Yay!
118:
Buddies? Listen, I don't call anyone a
friend unless they have a tail.
130:
AND they have to breathe under...
You're breathing underwater now,
aren't you?
135:
What should I call you? Saarcastic?
Ceasaar? Saarsy? I have waaay too
many ideas upstairs.
